items.name: Combined Systems Technology, Inc.
items.description:
A privately held company, Combined Systems Technology (CST) was founded in 1980. Combined Systems Technology CST designs and delivers Information Technology (IT) solutions which integrate architecture, engineering, hardware, software, and services that support our client’s business processes. We operate in Iowa within a broad range of markets in both the public and private sectors. CST uses a range of engineering and technology expertise to unify and simplify our clients' information technology. 

We help our clients gain a competitive advantage by deploying proven technology solutions to make their businesses more resilient to market opportunities and threats. When we improve the IT infrastructure availability for our clients, they often strengthen relationships with their customers by improving productivity and reduce information technology costs. We tend not to work with contracts but usually rely on our day to day performance.

CST actively supports 400 clients with day to day technology support. There are over 300 other clients that depend on CST for IT products and services. Additionally we provide specialized print systems for thousands of auto dealership customers in our dealer division. CST has been in business for over 36 years and has supported IT networks for all of those years. We have many satisfied clients that been with us 12 to 15 years having the same engineer and salesperson team assisting them.  CST employs 30 full-time staff in our Clive office and have no part time employees or contractors at this time. CST, however, has a small list of strategic partners that we leverage to provide specialized technologies services.

Many of our client partners are small- to medium-size professional firms who realize the importance of technology but do not possess the resources for a dedicated IT staff. Wearing many hats is a job requirement in small business; however, devoting sufficient time to address IT incidents without ignoring the core business is next to impossible. Clients find they can rely on CST to provide them with a comprehensive solution that meets their requirements.   Put simply, we provide the IT conduit that enables our clients to grow and prosper.

items.name: South Seas Data LLC
items.description:
PROVIDING CUSTOM SERVICE SOLUTIONS FOR OVER TWO DECADES
South Seas Data (SSD) established in 1992, located in Englewood, Colorado, has been serving Fortune 500 companies for over a couple of decades, providing efficient and highly qualified service solutions to the technology market. Point of sale (POS), equipment replacement and maintenance solutions for payment terminals and PC Hardware has been our primary focus. We have developed the advanced exchange and depot maintenance services to the highest degree of speed and efficiency. 

South Seas Data has expanded its service offerings to include an array of Cloud Hosted Solutions that will be applicable to the Small and Medium Business market as well as our current Point of Sale customer base.  These solutions address Private Cloud Hosted Virtual Desktops and Servers (DaaS), Disaster Recovery and Business Continuity (DRaaS), as well as remote and offsite backup solutions.

South Seas Data maintains many levels of certifications and manufacturer partnerships where we can leverage those relationships and provide support and solutions to our clients. Here at South Seas Data we like to maintain a variety of educational backgrounds which directly translates to not only a more educated workforce, but a greater knowledge base that can be leveraged to assist with your needs.

items.name: DYMIN SYSTEMS INC
items.description:
Dymin Systems is central Iowa’s leader for managed IT services, voice and cloud services, and both residential and commercial computer sales and support.

In 2001, Scott Breitman and William Stasak founded Dymin Systems on the revolutionary premise that computer services could be done accurately, affordably, on a timeline that customers would applaud. In the last 15 years, the success of our retail, residential, and outsourced business support has grown by leaps and bounds!

Our 5,000 square foot facility is located in Urbandale, Iowa, serving the Des Moines metropolitan area and the greater five-state region. We offer the largest showroom in the area of new and refurbished computer systems and parts, staffed by skilled IT service professionals. Our 18 employees include 15 IT technicians and engineers, allowing our in-house repair department to support up to 18 simultaneous bench repair jobs and our business support center to support up to eight simultaneous remote service calls! We have resources that rival the “big box” service providers with a level of personal service that they just can’t provide.

items.name: STERLING LEDET & ASSOCIATES INC
items.description:
Ledet Training operates and maintains instructor-led software training centers with multiple dedicated computer labs in Atlanta, Chicago, Denver, Houston, San Diego and Washington DC.  We also deliver virtual instructor-led training events in online classrooms and private instructor-led training events onsite at client locations.

Our training centers are full-time, long-term conventional commercial office leases. We are headquartered in Atlanta Georgia where we own a 10,200 sf corporate headquarters building and training center.

We are authorized training partners for Adobe, Autodesk, Microsoft, Filemaker, Unity Technologies and several smaller software vendors.

We serve a large variety of corporate and organizational clients across a broad swath of industries. Much of our clientele is government, military and academic in addition to public and private businesses. The majority of our class participants are employed professionals whose employer is investing in and sponsoring professional skills development and continuing education for their staff.

Ledet Training was founded in 1996. For two decades, we've been one of Adobe's largest authorized training centers, as well as being Autodesk, and Microsoft authorized. We've operated software training centers inside the commercial facilities of Apple Computer, QuarkXPress, and Fuji Film.
